+# Task 1 Report: CSS Restructure
+
+## Files Created
+- `css/base.css` ΓÇö reset, :root variables, body, .sr-only, .hidden, tab-content, grid layouts (cards-grid, charts-row, energy-tdl-grid, config-grid), section containers, filter-bar, responsive breakpoints, prefers-reduced-motion
+- `css/components.css` ΓÇö navbar, cards (base + renamed variants), chart boxes, period filter, filter buttons, config panel, toggle switch, buttons (save/capture/ac), capture UI, section-title, :focus-visible
+
+## Files Modified
+- `css/style.css` ΓÇö rewritten as two `@import` lines (`base.css` + `components.css`)
+
+## Summary of Changes
+1. **Reorganized** monolithic `style.css` (440 lines) into two modular files
+2. **Renamed card classes** from presentational to semantic:
+   - `.card-blue` ΓåÆ `.card-daya`
+   - `.card-teal` ΓåÆ `.card-energi`
+   - `.card-purple` ΓåÆ `.card-thi`
+   - `.card-pink` ΓåÆ `.card-cop`
+   - `.card-orange` ΓåÆ `.card-suhu`
+   - `.card-lavender` ΓåÆ `.card-kelembaban`
+   - `.card-green` ΓåÆ `.card-pir`
+   - `.card-red` ΓåÆ `.card-ac`
+3. **Removed** all `.grafik-grid` and `.chart-box-wide` rules (dead code for the removed Grafik tab; the first block lines 218ΓÇô242 was overridden by lines 245ΓÇô260 anyway)
+4. **Added** new classes per spec: `.hidden`, `.section-title`, `:focus-visible` on interactive elements, responsive queries, `prefers-reduced-motion`
+5. All visual values (colors, gradients, spacing, fonts, transitions) kept **exactly** as in the original `style.css`
+
+## Concerns
+1. **Card class naming vs. brief "Mapping aman":** The brief's "Mapping aman" section assigns `.card-orange` ΓåÆ `.card-kelembaban` and `.card-lavender` ΓåÆ `.card-suhu`, but the HTML (`index.html` lines 46ΓÇô52) shows card-orange = "Suhu Ruangan" (temperature) and card-lavender = "Kelembaban Ruangan" (humidity). I used the **semantically correct** mapping matching the HTML labels. If the brief was intentionally different, revert card-suhu Γåö card-kelembaban.
+2. **index.html not updated:** This task only touched CSS files. The HTML still uses old class names (`card-blue`, `card-teal`, etc.). A separate task must update `index.html` to use the renamed classes or the dashboard will lose card gradient styling.
+3. **No tests:** Per project conventions, there are no automated tests to verify visual fidelity.
diff --git a/css/base.css b/css/base.css
new file mode 100644
